tooca-l1-laser-engraver/assembly-tutoria.title: Assembly Tutorials
tooca-l1-laser-engraver/assembly-tutoria.description: 1. Install the left Y-axis assembly: Pass the left Y-axis assembly (with the timing belt upward) through the X-axis assembly, and thread the timing belt in the direction shown in the figure.

tooca-l1-laser-engraver/case-01-christma.title: Case 01: The Christmas Tree
tooca-l1-laser-engraver/case-01-christma.description: A Christmas tree is an evergreen tree decorated with lighted candles and decorations of firs or cedars. As one of the important components of Christmas, the modern Christmas tree originated in Germany and gradually became popular worldwide, becoming one of the most famous traditions in Christmas celebrations.

tooca-l1-laser-engraver/case-02-the-worl.title: Case 02: The World Map
tooca-l1-laser-engraver/case-02-the-worl.description: The World Map (The World Map) is a map depicting the entire surface of the earth, usually with topography, latitude and longitude lines, and other data such as place names, etc. Users can use the latitude and longitude lines to find out the specific location of each place on the world map, so as to understand the whole world. There are various ways to project the earth's surface onto a flat surface. Make a world map puzzle by yourself with TOOCA L1 Laser Engraver.

tooca-l1-laser-engraver/case-03-the-elk.title: Case 03: The Elk
tooca-l1-laser-engraver/case-03-the-elk.description: The elk is a large herbivore with a black longitudinal stripe on the back of the neck and a brownish-white belly and rump, and after September the body fur is replaced by a longer, thicker gray winter coat.

tooca-l1-laser-engraver/case-04-balancin.title: Case 04: Balancing Birds
tooca-l1-laser-engraver/case-04-balancin.description: A toy that uses the beak of the bird to stop on your finger. No matter where you put the bird (where you can place it or on your finger), it can balance and stabilize without falling. Like a real bird to fly.

tooca-l1-laser-engraver/case-05-the-cale.title: Case 05: The Calendar
tooca-l1-laser-engraver/case-05-the-cale.description: The calendar is a publication for daily use, recording dates and other relevant information.

tooca-l1-laser-engraver/case-06-the-halb.title: Case 06: Halberd Dragon
tooca-l1-laser-engraver/case-06-the-halb.description: The halberd dragon, also called spiny shield horned dinosaur, lived in the late Cretaceous period, is a kind of phytophagous horned dinosaur, the neck shield Halberd dragon's head is large, and the neck has a beautiful shield-shaped ring-shaped ornament. The shield ornaments around the long horn of six different sizes, constitute the Halberd dragon that big scary neck shield, this neck shield can not only scare the enemy. This neck shield generally grows spectacularly beautiful in strong and powerful males but is not developed in females, so experts speculate that its role is mainly for a display to attract the attention of the opposite sex. Because this neck shield looks very much like the ancient Chinese weapon in the halberd, it was figuratively named the halberd dragon. The strong limbs of the halberd dragon support the huge body. The horns of the halberd dragon and the bone spikes of the neck shield are like a sharp sword, which is a terrible weapon to turn defense into attack. The beak like a parrot's curved beak can cut to feed on the leaves of low plants. The halberd dragon's snout horn, about 60 cm long, is the main weapon when attacking.

tooca-l1-laser-engraver/case-07-the-tyra.title: Case 07: Tyrannosaurus Rex
tooca-l1-laser-engraver/case-07-the-tyra.description: The tyrannosaurus rex, or Rex Tyrannosaurus, survived in the Maastrichtian (MAA) period at the end of the Cretaceous about 68.5 to 65 million years ago at the very end of the Cretaceous and was one of the last non-avian species of the dinosaur before the Cretaceous-Tertiary extinction event. Fossils are found in the United States and Canada in North America, and it is one of the most recently extinct dinosaurs. Make a Tyrannosaurus Rex assembled model with a laser cutter.

tooca-l1-laser-engraver/case-08-the-penc.title: Case 08: The Pencil Holder of the Minions
tooca-l1-laser-engraver/case-08-the-penc.description: A pen holder is a columnar container for holding pens or other long stationery, and comes in a variety of shapes and materials. Traditional penholders are made of wood, stone, pottery, bamboo, and other materials.

tooca-l1-laser-engraver/case-09-the-cute.title: Case 09: The Cutebot Unicorn
tooca-l1-laser-engraver/case-09-the-cute.description: The unicorn appears in large numbers in June to August, with a tendency to light, mostly day and night, often gathered in the daytime at the sap flow of green oak, or in the light wax trees also often appear to gather hundreds of unicorns, at night, in mountainous areas with street lights, can often find their traces. They mainly feed on the sap of tree wounds, or ripe fruit, and basically do not cause harm to crops and trees.

tooca-l1-laser-engraver/case-10-the-farm.title: Case 10: The Farm Protection Devices
tooca-l1-laser-engraver/case-10-the-farm.description: In order to protect the farmlands from people to get in, we can set a farmland protection device.

tooca-l1-laser-engraver/Download-and-ins.title: LaserGRBL User Guide
tooca-l1-laser-engraver/Download-and-ins.description: Use a dust-free cloth with alcohol to wipe the protective lens of the laser module before engraving to ensure the best engraving effect.

tooca-l1-laser-engraver/elecfreaks-tooca.title: ELECFREAKS TOOCA L1 Laser Engraver
tooca-l1-laser-engraver/elecfreaks-tooca.description: The TOOCA L1 Laser Engraver with groundbreaking technologies, is capable of carving metal and almost all types of materials in large areas, bringing all your projects, including school projects, to life. Press the glowing button to control working status, including preview, engrave/cut, pause, and restart.

tooca-l1-laser-engraver/Materia-usage-gu.title: Material usage guidance
tooca-l1-laser-engraver/Materia-usage-gu.description: Warning: Since many materials are very dangerous when processed by laser, you need to be vigilant about processing them. Understand the hazards and please take precautions if necessary.

tooca-l1-laser-engraver/recognize-tooca-.title: Notes on Use
tooca-l1-laser-engraver/recognize-tooca-.description: Laser engraving machines use a high-density laser beam to irradiate materials when engraving or cutting them, creating high temperatures on the surface of the material with the goal of vaporizing the material without burning it. However, most materials are flammable by nature and may ignite and create an open flame which may burn the machine and its surroundings.
